<div
  class="mb-30 mt-30 rounded-xl hero min-h-auto"
  style="background-image: url(https://img.daisyui.com/images/stock/photo-1507358522600-9f71e620c44e.webp);"
>
  <div class="hero-overlay rounded-xl"></div>
  <div class="hero-content text-neutral-content text-center">
    <div class="max-w-md">
      <p class="mb-5 text-4xl font-bold text-white italic">
        Helpful feedback should leave someone with a clearer understanding of their behaviour and a practical sense of what to do next
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>





	
<h1 class="mb-15 mt-30 text-4xl font-bold text-center">Four qualities of helpful feedback</h1>


<main class="flex-grow">
  
  <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-6 pb-8">
    
    <div class="card bg-base-100 w-full shadow-sm">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title">It is specific</h2>
        <p>Helpful feedback focuses on a clear behaviour or example. It describes what happened rather than making broad statements.</p>
      </div>
      <figure>
        <img class=" p-[30px] w-1/5" src="../src/images/location.svg" alt="Shoes" />
      </figure>
    </div>

     <div class="card bg-base-100 w-full shadow-sm">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title">It is timely</h2>
        <p>Feedback is most useful when it is given close enough to the event that the details are still clear. Waiting too long can reduce its value and make the conversation harder.

Timely feedback allows the person to reflect while the situation is still fresh and apply changes sooner.</p>
      </div>
      <figure>
        <img class=" p-[30px] w-1/5" src="../src/images/clock.svg" alt="Shoes" />
      </figure>
    </div>

    <div class="card bg-base-100 w-full shadow-sm">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title">It is respectful</h2>
        <p>Helpful feedback shows respect for the other person. It focuses on behaviour, not character, and it is delivered in a calm and constructive way.

Respectful feedback does not attack, embarrass, or judge. Its purpose is to support improvement, not to win an argument or make someone feel small.</p>
      </div>
      <figure>
        <img class=" p-[30px] w-1/5" src="../src/images/heart.svg" alt="Shoes" />
      </figure>
    </div>

     <div class="card bg-base-100 w-full shadow-sm">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title">It focuses on behaviour, not personality</h2>
        <p>Helpful feedback talks about what someone did, not who they are. This is important because behaviour can be changed. Personality labels often feel personal and unfair.

Instead of:
“You are careless.”

Try:
“There were two errors in the final document, which meant we had to correct and resend it.”</p>
      </div>
      <figure>
        <img class=" p-[30px] w-1/5" src="../src/images/psychology.svg" alt="Shoes" />
      </figure>
    </div>

  </div>

 <!-- <Button>Tailwind Button in Astro!</Button>-->
</main>


	<h1 class="text-4xl pb-[70px] text-center font-bold mt-[60px]">Helpful vs unhelpful feedback</h1>
	<!--<p class="text-gray-500 pb-[40px]">By the end of this short course, you will be able to:</p>-->


<div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
  <Flip frontTitle="Unhelpful" frontText="“You need to be more professional.”" backTitle="Helpful" backText="“In yesterday’s workshop, you arrived 15 minutes late and the session had already started. In future, arriving earlier will help the session begin smoothly.”" />
  <Flip frontTitle="Unhelpful" frontText="Front text" backTitle="Helpful" backText="“The report was clear overall, but the recommendations section needed more evidence to support the points being made.”" />
  <Flip frontTitle="Unhelpful" frontText="Front text" backTitle="Helpful" backText="“In the planning meeting, you interrupted others several times, which made it harder for everyone to contribute.”" />
</div>


<h1 class="text-4xl pb-[70px] text-center font-bold mt-30">A simple check before giving feedback</h1>
<!--<p class="text-center mb-15">Before giving feedback, pause and ask yourself:</p>-->

<ul>
  <li><p class="italic text-xl text-center font-bold">Am I being clear about the behaviour?</p></li>
  
  <div class="divider"></div>
  <li><p class="italic text-xl text-center font-bold">Am I giving this feedback soon enough?</p></li>
  
  <div class="divider"></div>
  <li><p class="italic text-xl text-center font-bold">Am I speaking respectfully?</p></li>
  
  <div class="divider"></div>
  <li><p class="italic text-xl text-center font-bold">Am I focusing on something the person can actually change?</li>

</ul>



<div
  class="mb-30 mt-30 rounded-xl hero min-h-auto"
  style="background-image: url(https://img.daisyui.com/images/stock/photo-1507358522600-9f71e620c44e.webp);"
>
  <div class="hero-overlay rounded-xl"></div>
  <div class="hero-content text-neutral-content text-center">
    <div class="max-w-md">
      <h1 class="mb-5 text-5xl font-bold">Reflection</h1>
      <p class="mb-5">
        Think about a time when you received feedback that was genuinely helpful.
      </p>
      <button class="btn btn-primary">Get Started</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

	

</div>



	
